This paper deals with efficient retrieval of spatial data, which is a common problem in database systems (cs.DB). The paper also proposes a new algorithm for skyline queries, which involves ranking and optimization, making it relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The algorithm is based on geometric principles, which suggests that it may also be relevant to computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also involves empirical comparisons of different algorithms, which is a common theme in information retrieval (cs.IR) and data structures (cs.DS).
